      "content": "I can help you draft a rejection email that conveys professionalism and kindness. Here's a sample:\n\n\"Dear [Candidate Name],\n\nWe wanted to express our sincere gratitude for taking the time to interview for the Senior Developer position at [Company Name]. We were impressed by your technical skills and passion for the field, and it was a pleasure to get to know you better during our conversations.\n\nAfter careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose skills and experience best align with our current needs. Please know that this decision is in no way a reflection on your abilities or potential as a developer.\n\nWe appreciate the interest you showed in our company and wish you the best of luck in your ongoing job search. We hope our paths will cross again in the future.\n\nBest regards,\n[Your Name]\"\n\nThis email aims to acknowledge the candidate's qualifications, express gratitude for their interest, and clearly communicate the decision without being overly negative or critical. Feel free to modify it to fit your company's tone and style.",
